{
  "texts": [
    "The model is instructed using the prompt in Appendix E.4 and outputs one of five verdicts: \"false,\" \"mostly false,\" \"half-true,\" \"mostly true,\" or \"true,\" based on PolitiFact's Truth-o-Meter.",
    "foot_6 5 Experiments and Results",
    "Fact-checking frames.",
    "Arslan et al. (2020) introduced 11 manually defined semantic frames to extend the long-running Berkeley FrameNet project (Baker et al., 1998).",
    "Annotations for 936 sentences containing 1,029 frame-evoking targets and 3,570 frame elements are included in their dataset along with the newly-defined frames."
  ]
}